collapsed.description: Rule that fires if an expression is visually abstracted

font-number.description: Explicit speaking of font for numbers

ellipsis.description: Speaking an open ended ellipsis in AndSoOn preference
ellipsis.example: a comma b comma and so on

ellipsis-andsoon.description: Speaking an intermediate ellipsis in AndSoOn preference
ellipsis-andsoon.example: a comma b comma and so on up to n

parameters.%1: Expression left of the vertical bar.
parameters.%2: The subscript to the right of the vertical bar

vbar-evaluated.description: Interprets an vertical with subscript as evaluation of an antiderivative
vbar-evaluated.example: F of x, evaluated at x equals 0

parameters.%1: Expression left of the vertical bar.
parameters.%2: The superscript to the right of the vertical bar
parameters.%3: The subscript to the right of the vertical bar

vbar-evaluated-both.description: Interprets an vertical with subscript as evaluation of an antiderivative
vbar-evaluated-both.example: F of x, evaluated at infinity, minus the same expression evaluated at 0

vbar-such-that.description: Vertical bar interpreted as such that

vbar-divides.description: Vertical bar interpreted as divides symbol

vbar-always-divides.description: Vertical bar interpreted as divides symbol, regardless of context

vbar-given.description: Vertical bar interpreted as given, e.g., in a set context

set-member.description: Set membership symbol within a set expression read in short form. Fallback rule.

set-member-member.description: Set membership symbol within a set expression read in short form. Interpreted as member of

set-member-element.description: Set membership symbol within a set expression read in short form. Interpreted as element of

set-member-in.description: Set membership symbol within a set expression read in short form. Interpreted as in

set-member-belongs.description: Set membership symbol within a set expression read in short form. Interpreted as belonging to

set-not-member.description: Set membership symbol inside a set expression read in short form. Interpreted as not member of. Fallback rule

set-not-member-member.description: Set membership symbol inside a set expression read in short form. Interpreted as not member of

set-not-member-element.description: Set membership symbol inside a set expression read in short form. Interpreted as not element of

set-not-member-in.description: Set membership symbol inside a set expression read in short form. Interpreted as not in

set-not-member-belongs.description: Set membership symbol inside a set expression read in short form. Interpreted as not belongs to

function-article.description: The article before a function. Rule ensures that the case is corrected.

function-article-fem.description: The feminine article before a function. Rule ensures that the case is corrected.

appl-simple.description: Function application of a single letter function like f, g, h.

parameters.%2: The argument, which is a fenced function application

appl-simple-fenced.description: Function application of a single letter function with argument being another function application

appl-times.description: Forces function applications to be read as juxtapositions

function-prefix.description: Application of a known prefix function, e.g., a trigonometric function

function-prefix-simple-arg.description: Application of a known prefix function to a fenced but simple argument (e.g., xy is simple, x + y is not)

function-prefix-embell.description: Application of a prefix function with index or superscript

function-prefix-fenced-or-frac-arg.description: Application of a prefix functions to a non-simple argument.
function-prefix-fenced-or-frac-arg.example: the sine of a over b

function-prefix-subscript.description: Function application of a named function with subscript

function-ln.description: Natural logarithm application in short speech.

function-ln-pause.description: Natural logarithm application with following pause.

function-ln-of.description: Natural logarithm application in explicit speech.

function-prefix-as-exp.description: Function in a superscript with a complex argument
function-prefix-as-exp.example: x raised to the sine of open paren y plus z close paren power

function-prefix-subscript-as-exp.description: Function in a subscript with a complex argument
function-prefix-subscript-as-exp.example: x sub the sine of open paren y plus z close paren

appl-triginverse.description: Speaks an arcus function as inverse

function-prefix-arc-simple.description: Speaks an inverse trigonometric function as arcus

parameters.%2: The fenced argument with simple content

function-prefix-arc-simple-fenced.description: Speaks an inverted trigonometric function as arcus. Omits the parentheses on simple arguments.

parameters.%2: The fenced argument with simple content

function-prefix-arc.description: Speaks an inverted trigonometric function as arcus. Fallback for complex arguments.
function-prefix-arc.example: arc sine of open paren x plus y close paren

superscript-prefix-function.description: General function with superscript that is either a number of simple identifier.

superscript.description: The fallback rule for superscript/exponent expressions

parameters.%2: The exponent as an integer or single letter identifier

superscript-ordinal.description: Fallback rule for exponent expressions with integer or simple single letter identifier exponent

superscript-ordinal-default.description: Fallback rule for exponent expressions in Ordinal preference.
superscript-ordinal-default.example: x raised to the y plus z power

superscript-simple-exponent.description: Rule for exponent expressions with single letter or integer exponents in Ordinal preference.

superscript-simple-exponent-end.description: Rule for exponent expressions with simple exponents where power is used as postfix for disambiguation.
superscript-simple-exponent-end.example: x raised to the 2 y power

superscript-non-ordinal.description: Rule for exponent expressions with simple exponents that should not be read a ordinals in Ordinal preference.

exponent.description: A letter spoken as ordinal exponent. Note that the rule might need adjustment of the join attribute.
exponent.example: y-th as in x to the y-th

exponent-number.description: A number spoken as an ordinal. Note that the rule might need adjustment of the join attribute.
exponent-number.example: fourth as in x to the fourth

exponent-zero.description: The exponent zero, or power zero.

parameters.%2: The adjective for squared, to put into its grammatically correct case, e.g., in Italian

parameters.%3: The overall interval for speaking specialisations, such as inclusions or exclusions of boundaries

fences-interval.description: A fenced pair of values interpreted as in interval. This is the base rule, specialisations are handled in subsequent rules.
fences-interval.example: The interval from a to b

parameters.%1: The element left of the divider

set-extended.description: A set defined via set intensionality
set-extended.example: The set of all a in A such that ...

set-collection.description: Set defined via a collection of elements
set-collection.example: The set a comma b comma c

parameters.%1: The element left of the divider

set-extended-woall.description: A set defined via set intensionality without an explicity for all
set-extended-woall.example: The set a in A such that ...

fraction.description: Fallback rule for explicit speaking of fraction
fraction.example: the fraction with numerator a and denominator b

parameters.%1: The vulgar fraction. Add pausing or grammar instructions if necessary.

vulgar-fraction.description: Vulgar fraction spoken as words. The rule fires for positive integer numerators <= 10 and denominators <=20

fraction-over.description: Short speech for fractions with simple components.

fraction-overendfrac.description: Short speech for fractions with simple components with explicit end fraction

fraction-fracover.description: Short speech for fractions with simple components with explicitly announced fraction

fraction-per.description: Short speech for fractions with simple components using per

division.description: An inline division with forward slash or division sign

parameters.%1: The content of the absolute value
The content of the absolute value

fences-neutral-absend.description: Absolute values spoken with explicit end of absolute value

parameters.%1: The content between the neutral fences

fences-neutral-cardinality.description: Neutral interpreted as cardinality of a set

parameters.%1: The content between the neutral fences

fences-neutral-determinant.description: Neutral interpreted as determinant of a matrix

unit-reciprocal.description: A unit to the power of negative one

german-font.description: A character in fraktur font. Fraktur is sometimes also called blackletter or gothic. In English it is called German rather then the font name. Most other locales do not need this rule.

parameters.%1: The character in bold fraktur font

german-font-bold.description: A character in bold fraktur font. Fraktur is sometimes also called blackletter or gothic. In English it is called German rather then the font name. Most other locales do not need this rule.

article.description: A leading article is introduced. Only used in locales where articles are used for fractions or functions

squared-masculine.description: Squared if base is grammatically of masculine gender

squared-feminine.description: Squared if base is grammatically of feminine gender

member.description: Set membership symbol not within a set expression. Interpreted as member of. This is the fallback rule.
member.example: a is a member of A

member-member.description: Set membership symbol not within a set expression. Interpreted as member of
member-member.example: a is a member of A

member-element.description: Set membership symbol not within a set expression. Interpreted as element of
member-element.example: a is an element of A

member-in.description: Set membership symbol not within a set expression. Interpreted as is in

member-belongs.description: Set membership symbol not within a set expression. Interpreted as is belongs to

not-member.description: Set membership symbol not within a set expression. Interpreted as not member of. Fallback rule
not-member.example: a is not a member of A

not-member-member.description: Set membership symbol not within a set expression. Interpreted as not member of
not-member-member.example: a is not a member of A

not-member-element.description: Set membership symbol not within a set expression. Interpreted as not element of
not-member-element.example: a is not an element of A

not-member-in.description: Set membership symbol not within a set expression. Interpreted as not in

not-member-belongs.description: Set membership symbol not within a set expression. Interpreted as not belong to
not-member-belongs.example: a does not belong to A
